1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:05,465
Some supporters belong to a city. This one belongs to no country at all.

2
00:00:05,515 --> 00:00:10,180
A wanderer with a suitcase of flags, who has stood in every stadium the game has ever known.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,150
Tonight, he finds his people.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,695
Last time, we predicted Haiti and Scotland would draw and dance.

5
00:00:20,745 --> 00:00:24,940
Tonight — two nations of wanderers, fighting for one place in the next round.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,515
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode eleven.

7
00:00:30,565 --> 00:00:34,080
Australia versus Turkey. The nomads' duel.

8
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:43,010
And stay with me — because in the eighty-eighth minute, one desperate header decides everything.

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:51,505
First, the wanderers.

10
00:00:51,555 --> 00:00:56,560
Australia — the island continent, football's great survivors, who in twenty twenty-two pushed Argentina to the very brink.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,450
And Mathew Ryan: their captain and goalkeeper, a man who has played in six leagues across four continents.

12
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:07,950
This is his fourth World Cup. Home, for him, is wherever he fights.

13
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:12,100
Turkey are wanderers too.

14
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:15,750
The bridge between East and West — and in two thousand two, they finished THIRD at a World Cup.

15
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:19,400
A golden age the country has been chasing ever since.

16
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:24,760
Their leader, Calhanoglu, left Turkey at eighteen and built an empire in Germany and Italy.

17
00:01:24,810 --> 00:01:29,070
Home is not where you are born — it is where you fight.

18
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,165
Tonight, one of these wanderers finds a home in the knockout rounds.

19
00:01:32,215 --> 00:01:34,880
The other goes back on the road.

20
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:42,910
Meet the Socceroos. Built on grit, running, and absolutely no fear.

21
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:47,960
Mathew Ryan, thirty-four, reflexes still razor-sharp.

22
00:01:48,010 --> 00:01:51,470
Harry Souttar guards the box like a castle wall.

23
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,980
And Jackson Irvine covers every blade of grass.

24
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,040
Survivors. Every single one of them.

25
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,560
This is Australia's last chance to define their tournament.

26
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,280
But Turkey carry the joy of a new golden generation, light on their feet and full of swagger.

27
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:31,100
Arda Guler drifts across the pitch like smoke — here, then gone, then appearing in the most dangerous space on the field.

28
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:38,115
Kenan Yildiz, the Juventus prodigy who chose Turkey over Germany, plays with pure joy.

29
00:02:38,165 --> 00:02:42,780
And Calhanoglu bends free kicks like gravity is optional.

30
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,290
Proving twenty-oh-two was no fluke — but a promise.

31
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,595
And the duel inside the match: Calhanoglu against Ryan. The conductor's free kick...

32
00:02:54,645 --> 00:02:59,740
against the keeper of six leagues. Set-piece against reflex.

33
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:06,610
Our prediction — built on grit, on swagger, and on one desperate header. Watch.

34
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,905
Turkey strike first. Yildiz dances inside and finishes. Then Guler bends one home.

35
00:03:12,955 --> 00:03:17,360
Two-one Turkey — and the clock is bleeding away.

36
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,770
But Australia have always been survivors. They throw everybody forward.

37
00:03:21,820 --> 00:03:25,690
And the clock crawls toward... the eighty-eighth minute.

38
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,877
Free kick, thirty-five yards.

39
00:03:29,927 --> 00:03:32,803
Every Socceroo pushes up — even Ryan, the goalkeeper, jogs to the edge of the box.

40
00:03:32,853 --> 00:03:35,730
The whole stadium rises.

41
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,560
The ball swings in. Souttar climbs above everyone —

42
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,890
HEADER! It arrows in! TWO—TWO!

43
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:50,830
The towering defender saves Australia in the final breath!

44
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,010
Full time in our story: two-two.

45
00:03:57,060 --> 00:04:01,070
Two nations of wanderers — and tonight, neither one goes home. The road continues.

46
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:07,070
Do you agree? Comment SOCCEROOS if Australia reach the knockouts again.

47
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:10,690
Comment CRESCENT if Turkey's golden age is back.

48
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,885
And the wanderer with the suitcase? Legend number eleven: The Wanderer.

49
00:04:17,935 --> 00:04:23,320
No nation, no home — just every World Cup, forever.

50
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,920
Tonight, he stood with both. Collect him inside the game.

51
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,313
Which brings us to YOU.

52
00:04:35,363 --> 00:04:38,177
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

53
00:04:38,227 --> 00:04:41,040
scores for you.

54
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:47,430
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple.

55
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,650
Hit like — send this to the friend who's always on the move.

56
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:57,150
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

